"title": "8341: separation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8341: separation",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A setting apart. Separation is at the heart of the biblical idea of holiness. God is separate from his creation and has set apart his people from the world. Sin causes alienation between God and humanity, making necessary the reconciling work of Jesus Christ. The end of the age will bring the final separation between the righteous and the wicked.</p>\n<h3>God is without equal</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:11\">EXO 15:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:6\">PSA 89:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:25-Isa40:26\">ISA 40:25–40:26</a></p>\n<h3>God is separate from his creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:22\">ISA 40:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:1\">GEN 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:16\">ISA 29:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:11-Isa45:12\">ISA 45:11–45:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:25\">ROM 1:25</a></p>\n<h2>The separateness of God's people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:6\">DEU 7:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:5-Exod19:6\">EXO 19:5–19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:2\">DEU 14:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:4\">PSA 135:4</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:9\">1PE 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:19-1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:19–6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Separation from the world</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:26\">LEV 20:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num23:9\">NUM 23:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:2\">NEH 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:28\">NEH 10:28</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:18-John15:19\">JHN 15:18–15:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:16\">JHN 17:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:20\">PHP 3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:11\">1PE 2:11</a></p>\n<h3>Separation from sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:17\">2CO 6:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:11\">ISA 52:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:31\">LEV 15:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:21\">EZR 6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:18\">1CO 6:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:34\">1CO 15:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:1\">2CO 7:1</a></p>\n<h3>Avoidance of evil association</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:33\">1CO 15:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:20\">PRO 13:20</a>DEU <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:2-Prov7:3\">7:2–7:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:7\">JOS 23:7</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:3\">EZR 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:11\">EZR 10:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:115\">PSA 119:115</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:14\">2CO 6:14</a></p>\n<h3>Excommunication</h3>\n<p>Israelites refusing to follow God's commands to be cut off from God's people:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:29\">LEV 18:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:30\">NUM 15:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:20\">NUM 19:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:15-Matt18:17\">MAT 18:15–18:17</a> <em>separation from unrepentant believers</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:17\">ROM 16:17</a> <em>separation from false teachers</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:9-1Cor5:13\">1CO 5:9–5:13</a> <em>separation from wilfully sinful believers</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:6\">2TH 3:6</a> <em>separation from wilfully disobedient believers</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:9-Titus3:11\">TIT 3:9–3:11</a> <em>separation from divisive people</em></p>\n<h3>Separation for service to God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:2-Num6:3\">NUM 6:2–6:3</a> <em>the Nazirites</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:9\">NUM 16:9</a> <em>the Levites</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:13\">1CH 23:13</a> <em>Aaron and his descendants</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr25:1\">1CH 25:1</a> <em>prophets</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:5\">JER 1:5</a> <em>Jeremiah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:1\">ROM 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:15\">GAL 1:15</a></p>\n<h3>Separation of holy places</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod26:33\">EXO 26:33</a> <em>the Most Holy Place separated by a curtain</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:7\">EXO 33:7</a> <em>the Tent of Meeting placed outside the camp</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek42:20\">EZK 42:20</a> <em>Ezekiel's temple separated by a wall</em></p>\n<h2>Separation caused by sin</h2>\n<h3>Separation from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:2\">ISA 59:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:13\">HAB 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:18\">EPH 4:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:21\">COL 1:21</a></p>\n<h3>Separation at the final judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:32-Matt25:33\">MAT 25:32–25:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:40-Matt13:42\">MAT 13:40–13:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:47-Matt13:50\">MAT 13:47–13:50</a></p>\n<h2>Separation of people from one another</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:16-Ruth1:17\">RUT 1:16–1:17</a> <em>Ruth will not be separated from Naomi</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs2:11\">2KI 2:11</a> <em>Elisha separated from Elijah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:15\">PHM 1:15</a> <em>Philemon separated from Onesimus</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:9\">JHN 4:9</a> <em>separation between Jews and Samaritans</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:11-Eph2:12\">EPH 2:11–2:12</a> <em>separation between Jews and Gentiles</em></p>\n<h3>The pain of separation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:37-Acts20:38\">ACT 20:37–20:38</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:41\">1SA 20:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:20\">JHN 16:20</a> <em>Jesus Christ foretells his death and resurrection</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:4\">2TI 1:4</a></p>\n<h3>The pain of separation through death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:2\">ACT 8:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:33-Gen37:35\">GEN 37:33–37:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:15\">JER 31:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:18\">MAT 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Husband and wife not to be separated</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:5-Matt19:6\">MAT 19:5–19:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:7-Mark10:9\">MRK 10:7–10:9</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:24\">GEN 2:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:10-1Cor7:13\">1CO 7:10–7:13</a></p>\n<h2>Reconciliation through Jesus Christ ends the separation from God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:18-2Cor5:20\">2CO 5:18–5:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:46\">MAT 27:46</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:34\">MRK 15:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:1\">PSA 22:1</a> <em>Reconciliation with God is possible because Jesus Christ bore the punishment of separation from God that human sin deserves</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:51\">MAT 27:51</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:38\">MRK 15:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:45\">LUK 23:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:35-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:35–8:39</a> <em>Nothing can separate believers from God's love shown in Christ</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14-Eph2:15\">EPH 2:14–2:15</a> <em>Jew and Gentile reconciled through mutual reconciliation to God</em></p>",
